plotting scatter plots with labels (first way)¶

In [30]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots()

data_subset = df[df["Species"] == 'Iris-setosa']
ax.scatter(data_subset['PetalLengthCm'].values, data_subset['SepalLengthCm'].values,label= "Iris-setosa")

data_subset = df[df["Species"] == 'Iris-virginica']
ax.scatter(data_subset['PetalLengthCm'].values, data_subset['SepalLengthCm'].values, label= "Iris-virginica")

data_subset = df[df["Species"] == 'Iris-versicolor']
ax.scatter(data_subset['PetalLengthCm'].values, data_subset['SepalLengthCm'].values, label = "Iris-versicolor")
ax.legend()
plt.show()
In [31]:
df['Species'].unique()
Out[31]:
array(['Iris-setosa', 'Iris-versicolor', 'Iris-virginica'], dtype=object)

alternative way¶

In [32]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
for target_species in df['Species'].unique():
    data_subset = df[df['Species'] == target_species]
    ax.scatter(data_subset['PetalWidthCm'].values, data_subset['SepalWidthCm'].values, label=target_species)
ax.legend()
plt.show()

section 5: using subplots¶

In [38]:
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2,2)

axes[0,0].plot(df['Species'],df['SepalLengthCm'])
axes[0,0].set_xlabel('Species')
axes[0,0].set_ylabel('SepallLengthCm')
axes[0,0].set_title('Sepal length against Species')

axes[0,1].bar(df['Species'],df['SepalLengthCm'])
axes[0,1].set_xlabel('Species')
axes[0,1].set_ylabel('SepallLengthCm')
axes[0,1].set_title('Sepal length against Species')


axes[1,0].hist(df['SepalLengthCm'])
axes[1,0].set_ylabel('SepallLengthCm')
axes[1,0].set_title('Sepal length against Species')

data_subset = df[df["Species"] == 'Iris-setosa']
axes[1,1].scatter(data_subset['PetalLengthCm'].values, data_subset['SepalLengthCm'].values,c="grey")
axes[1,1].set_xlabel('Petal length')
axes[1,1].set_ylabel('SepallLength')
axes[1,1].set_title('Petal length against sepal length')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

ax.set_title('x vs y',fontsize=20)

# How to set grids in a graph
In [55]:
x= np.arange(-5,5,0.1)
y= x**5
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,5))

ax.plot(x,y)
ax.set_xlabel('x-label',fontsize=20,color='red')
ax.set_ylabel('y-label',fontsize=20)
ax.set_title('x vs y',fontsize=20)

ax.grid(True)
plt.show()
